2. The net addition in cash and cash equivalents during the period

### Balance Sheet
Looking at the Balance Sheet, I see "Interest Receivable" with an end amount of 14,575.80. This represents interest that has accrued but has not yet been received.

### Cash Flow Statement
In the Cash Flow Statement, I can see "Net Increase" in Cash and Cash Equivalents with a value of -650,630.22. This represents the net change in cash and cash equivalents during the period.

### Income Statement
The Income Statement shows "Interest Income" of 14,575.80, which matches the Interest Receivable on the Balance Sheet, confirming this is the accrued interest.

Therefore:
- Value 1 (interest accrued but not yet received): 14,575.80
- Value 2 (net addition in cash and cash equivalents): -650,630.22
